The Police Command in Benue State on Wednesday exhumed an unknown decomposed body in a rice farm in Ukum Local Government Area of the State. The Public Relations Officer (PPRO) of the command, Ms Catherine Anene who confirmed the incident to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Makurdi said she was yet to get full details of the operation. Anene, however, stated that the body was on transit to Makurdi, the state capital, adding that the media would be briefed accordingly. “Yes, we have exhumed a decomposed body; for now we are yet to get full details,” she said. DAILY POST recalls that the command on September 26 exhumed 11 bodies in Ushongo Local Government Area and arrested six suspects who are already facing prosecution in the state. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.